========================================================================
C21 vs C22: ACCUM ECHO vs EXOGENOUS INJECTION
========================================================================

  C21 (Option A — accum_reg echo):   max CPR = 1.36%,  r(coupling,computed)=0.97
    → coupling carries arithmetic history (highly correlated with computed)
    → no new attractor structure, no MI from state

  C22 (Option B — exogenous XOR):    max MI_obs=0.0045 bits, max CPR=0.2580
    → coupling carries no arithmetic history (independent LFSR source)
    → large MI_obs because XOR directly controls E-field bits
    → but MI_arith = 0: arithmetic computation is unchanged

  KEY INSIGHT: Observer controllability ≠ computational causal influence.
  You can STEER what an observer classifies as attractor states
  without changing a single bit of the arithmetic computation.

